Patrolling policeman made the grim discovery during a routine patrol in the township, south of Johannesburg, on Thursday morning. JOHANNESBURG - The parents of a decapitated two-month-old baby who was found in Thokoza have still not come forward.Patrolling policeman made the grim discovery during a routine patrol in the township, south of Johannesburg, on Thursday morning.Community leader Mdzipo Kalipa says residents are shocked about the killing. Social workers from Ekurhuleni has taken responsibility of counselling all the witnesses. There are about five witnesses, including my aunt. 